'''[[赛义德|赛义德]]·巴德尔·本·哈马德·本·哈姆德·布赛义迪'''（Sayyid Badr bin Hamad bin Hamood Al Busaidi {{bd|1960年|5月30日}}）是[[阿曼|阿曼]]的外交部长<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-oman-government-idUKKCN25E1PY|title=Oman transfers powers from Sultan's remit in government revamp|date=August 18, 2020|via=uk.reuters.com|access-date=2021-03-22|archive-date=2020-09-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200902124901/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-oman-government-idUKKCN25E1PY|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newsbriefsoman.info/category/omani-government/blogid/2 |title=News Brief Oman |access-date=2021-03-22 |archive-date=2013-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019095103/http://www.newsbriefsoman.info/category/omani-government/blogid/2 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://encyclopedia.jrank.org/articles/pages/5489/Al-Bu-Sa-id-Badr-Bin-Hamad-Bin-Hamood-1960.htm|title=Al Bu Sa'id, Badr Bin Hamad Bin Hamood (1960–) - PERSONAL HISTORY, INFLUENCES AND CONTRIBUTIONS, BIOGRAPHICAL HIGHLIGHTS, PERSONAL CHRONOLOGY:, THE WORLD’S PERSPECTIVE, LEGACY|website=encyclopedia.jrank.org}}</ref>。

== 生平 ==

他出生于阿曼的[[马斯喀特|马斯喀特]]，是家中次子，他的父亲曾是苏丹[[赛义德·本·泰穆尔|赛义德·本·泰穆尔]]的私人秘书<ref>{{cite web|url=http://encyclopedia.jrank.org/articles/pages/5489/Al-Bu-Sa-id-Badr-Bin-Hamad-Bin-Hamood-1960.html|title=Al Bu Sa'id, Badr Bin Hamad Bin Hamood (1960–) - PERSONAL HISTORY, INFLUENCES AND CONTRIBUTIONS, BIOGRAPHICAL HIGHLIGHTS, PERSONAL CHRONOLOGY:, THE WORLD’S PERSPECTIVE, LEGACY|website=encyclopedia.jrank.org|access-date=2021-03-22|archive-date=2017-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222051422/http://encyclopedia.jrank.org/articles/pages/5489/Al-Bu-Sa-id-Badr-Bin-Hamad-Bin-Hamood-1960.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他本人则也做过苏丹[[卡布斯·本·赛义德·阿勒赛义德|卡布斯·本·赛义德·阿勒赛义德]]的私人顾问。他在1988年开始于阿曼外交部任职，成为一名外交官。2020年8月18日，他开始担任阿曼外交部长。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Reuters|date=2020-08-18|title=Oman Transfers Powers From Sultan's Remit in Government Revamp|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/08/18/world/middleeast/18reuters-oman-government.html|access-date=2020-08-18|issn=0362-4331}}{{Dead link}}</ref>

